Develop with CRM Analytics

You can enable object-specific actions and global actions that you previously defined on Salesforce objects directly from CRM Analytics. Lens and dashboard viewers can invoke these actions to create, update, and interact with Salesforce records.

Perform Actions on a Salesforce Record from CRM Analytics
As you gain insights into your business from CRM Analytics, you sometimes perform actions on an underlying Salesforce record. You can invoke a Salesforce action on the record directly from CRM Analytics.
You can also open web pages, such as search the web for the company name listed in a CRM Analytics lens or dashboard.

Perform Bulk Actions on Multiple Salesforce Records from CRM Analytics
Sometimes, you need to perform the same action on a group of records. With CRM Analytics bulk actions, you can perform an action on all records shown in a table in CRM Analytics.
Configure Mass Quick Actions on Multiple Salesforce Records from CRM Analytics Dashboards
Users can save time by performing a quick action on up to 100 records at once from a step in CRM Analytics.

Enable Actions for CRM Analytics Lenses and Dashboards

You are here: Enable Actions for CRM Analytics Lenses and Dashboards

Let users take action on insights directly from CRM Analytics. Add actions to charts and tables in lenses and dashboards.
Selecting a Salesforce record action in a CRM Analytics dashboard opens the record in a new Lightning Experience tab.

Note: To open in a new browser tab, select the Open Salesforce records in new browser tabs setting in Setup.
title: Enabling Actions in Salesforce CRM Analytics
